title: For Sale:  Complete 18" 1MOA Daniel Defense S2W CHF barrel ar 15 upper receiver
location: West chase area / west houston, Houston, Texas
postcontent:
For sale is a complete 18" upper receiver WITHOUT THE CHARGING HANDLE for an ar15. Technically not a complete upper, but essentially complete. The barrel is an 18" Daniel Defense Strength to Weight barrel mid length gas(https://danieldefense.com/cold-hammer-forged-barrels/18-5-56mm-s2w-mid-length-chf-barrel-stripped.html)  with a Larue Tactical 12" rail. Young Manufacturing chrome National Match complete Bolt carrier group. I have had great success with Young MFG bolts. The upper is a Red X arms upper receiver with forward assist. Rear takedown pin hole has very slight shaving on the inside of the hole due to a fitting issue I had with one of my lowers. It sits atop my other lowers with no fitment issues. The gas block is a VLTOR stainless steel low profile gas block. The rail will come with 3 ladder style rail covers. They are on the rail in the picture but are a bit hard to see.

I have had great accuracy with this upper. My best group was 1/2in. and the average is 1-1.5in at 100 yards. Never shot it past 200 yards but I would expect it to hold 1MOA at 300 yards. The barrel has had aproximately 700 rounds through it, so its just now getting well broken in. I cleaned it very well after each use with an inital 50 round break in consisting of firing one shot, cleaning after each consecutive shot for 5 rounds. Then Firing 5 rounds and cleaning. Then 10 rounds and cleaning and so on. This obsessive break in method may be superstition, but the barrel does shoot well.

ALL OF MY GROUPS WERE SHOT WITH HONADY 60gr VMAX rounds on top of 22gr of Hodgdon 335 powder with lake city brass. This barrel faired very well with the 60gr bullets. As to be expected, do not expect .5-1in moa accuracy when using surplus or mass production ammunition. Match grade ammunition or hand loads would be a nice choice for obtaining such accuracy.


ITEMS NOT INCLUDED IN SALE : muzzle break, rail mounted bipod adapter.

ASKING 650$

The barrel and rail alone are worth $600

If you have any more questions or want to see more pictures, please let me know. I realize the full picture of the rail is a bit on the grainy side. I will try and get a new picture for it. But please dont hesitate to ask to see more, i have many up close pictures.

I am located around beltway 8 and westpark tollway on the west side of houston. I am willing to drive a reasonable distance if necessary so let me know where you are located and we can work something out.

I also have this ad posted on texasguntrader.com under the name francomatic.

title: For Sale:  Model 1916 Spanish Mauser, w/ ammo, bayonet, and accessories
postcontent:
1926 Spanish Mauser (Model 1916).  21" barrel, chambered in the original 7x57mm (7mm Mauser).  Serial numbers are on the receiver and the barrel, and they match.  Comes with nice leather sling, 95 rounds of new-production re-loadable ammo, bayonet, and cleaning accessories.

  Rifle has all-original parts from what I can tell.  1926 was the only year the Lange Vizier rear sight was used on this rifle, which makes it something of a rarity.  The stock has been re-finished in Tung oil, and is a perfect match to the original.  Most of the original bluing is gone, and there is some pitting on some of the metal parts, but nothing that will affect safety or functionality.

  I have not shot this rifle, so I cannot tell you how it groups.  The Crown looks good to me, and the strong rifling and good trigger makes me think that it'll be a pretty good shooter.

  The Bayonet appears to be a Model 1917, and has quite a bit of erosion on the blade, but is still functional and fits the very nicely.  One of the wood handles has a repaired crack.

  60 rounds of ammo are new-in-box, and 35 are reloads from a professional manufacturer, loaded to factory specs.  The cleaning supplies are some brand-new nylon and brass brushes, some used brushes, and an aluminum jag.

  Price is $200.00 even, and I am located in Conyers, GA.  I'm willing to travel about an hour to meet up, and do not want to ship.  Breakdown of price is $150.00 for the rifle, $40.00 for the ammo, $10.00 for the bayonet.  This model in similar shape seems to go for around $250-$350 by itself, and that's with the typical leaf sight from other production years.

title: For Sale:  New Browning X-Bolt
postcontent:
The X-Bolt White Gold is beautifully adorned with a polished Stainless steel receiver that is drilled and tapped for scope mounts with Engravings both the front and rear. This rifle also has a polished Stainless steel barrel. Its stock is a gloss-finished, finely Checkered with a rosewood forend and grip cap. 
• Monte Carlo stock places the recoil pad directly in line with the shoulder, resulting in less perceived recoil for more comfortable shooting.
• The high grade Walnut stock with detailed checkering provides classic good looks.
• A durable gloss finish provides protection and enhances the natural beauty of the hardwood.
• Rosewood caps on the fore-end and grip offer additional elegance.
• Innovative Inflex Technology recoil pad uses directional deflection to pull the stock down and away from the face to reduce perceived recoil. 
• Barrel, action, trigger guard and other metal surfaces feature polished Stainless steel for a striking appearance.
• Button-rifled barrel is triple checked for quality and individually hand chambered and air gauged to ensure consistency and accuracy.
• The target Crown enables the uniform release of gas as the bullet exits the barrel, preventing a shift in trajectory. The Crown is recessed to protect it from accidental damage that degrades accuracy.
• Free floated barrel eliminates contact interference from the fore-end, enabling the superior barrel craftsmanship to perform consistently and accurately.
• Drilled and tapped for X-Lock scope mounts that use four screws for each base to provide a rock solid optic platform.
• Adjustable Feather Trigger minimizes the "human factor" by eliminating creep and take-up — providing a crisp trigger pull that "breaks like glass."
• Low profile action allows you to mount the scope extremely close to the center of the bore to minimize the offset between point of aim and Point of Impact.
• 60° bolt lift keeps the thumb and fingers clear of the scope when cycling the action and allows the bolt to be operated in a smoother/quicker motion.
• Top-tang safety offers easy accessibility without removing your firing hand from the stock. The shooter can quickly manipulate the safety, or verify the position of the safety, without losing your sight picture or cheek weld.
• Detachable Rotary magazine is built from tough polymer and is designed to stop forward movement of the cartridge by contacting the shoulder of the case rather than the tip of the projectile. This prevents bullet tip deformation and recoil induced bullet seating depth change.
• Bolt Unlock Button allows the bolt to be cycled with the safety engaged.

Feinwerkbau AW93 target pistol

AW93, original model, with 2 magazines

These guns are "From Russian with Love", a Soviet design, perfected and made since 1993 in Germany.  They are the preferred pistol of most of the US Military marksmanship teams.

The trigger is two stage, but the first stage can be nearly completely removed.  Trigger positon, weight, and preload all are adjustable.  Accuracy is nearly as good as the Hammerli 208.l

$1580 for gun, 2 magazines, original manual and test target.

Factory case (not original to the gun) $100 additional

As an older model, this gun has no magazine activated hold open (unless the magazine is modified). Any AW93 magazine (one designed for hold open, or not) will work with the gun.

Additional magazines available with the gun (up to 4) at $120 each.

A similar gun, but with magazine activated hold open alsi is available, at higher price. The older AW93 tend to be more accurate than the current production. They have a hammer block safety that serves as a dry fire device, and use the same recoil buffers (See first image, for the hammer block and dry fire function). The grip for these original AW93 are slightly different due to the side activated hold open. The more recent AW93 grips require some modification to fit this gun.

The AW93 is not well suited for small hands. Rink however does make grips that are downsized as much as possible for smaller hands or shorter fingers.

Shipping is extra, usually around $30.

FFL transfer only.
